<subSubSection id="C306789DFFCFFF9E6BB0FA58FDDAF92F" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCFFF9E6BB0FA58FC27FA5E" blockId="5.[151,1436,1430,1671]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
This species was reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6937FA58FD74FA07" box="[528,682,1430,1455]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E699EFA58FCD0FA07" box="[697,782,1430,1455]" name="Kuwait" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E683AFA58FBC5FA07" box="[797,1051,1430,1455]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6F09FA58FBB5FA07" box="[1070,1131,1430,1455]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">UAE</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFCFFF9E6F96FA58FB2BFA07" box="[1201,1269,1430,1455]" name="Oman" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Oman</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6E2FFA58FF0CFA7B" author="Collingwood, C. A." pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6BFAFA74FDEDFA7B" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D." box="[221,563,1466,1491]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref6843" refString="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. (1996) Formicidae of Saudi Arabia (Part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 15, 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6919FA74FC8FFA7B" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. &amp; Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T." box="[574,849,1466,1491]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="405 - 474" refId="ref6877" refString="Collingwood, C. A., Agosti, D., Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Van Harten T. (2011) Order Hymenoptera, Family Formicidae. Arthropod Fauna of the UAE, 4, 405 - 474." type="journal article" year="2011">
Collingwood 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E69F0FA75FCD1FA7B" box="[727,783,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). Foragers are common from March to October with a peak in September. Workers were commonly found foraging on 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E685DFA11FC2FFA5E" box="[890,1009,1503,1526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E685DFA11FC2FFA5E" box="[890,1009,1503,1526]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">C. procera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFCFFF9E6BE0F9CCFDDAF92F" blockId="5.[151,1436,1430,1671]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
The high degree of polymorphism and the large intra- and interspecific variation among the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6BB0F9E9FEFBF996" authorityName=": Mayr" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,293,1575,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6BB0F9E9FEFBF996" box="[151,293,1575,1598]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Camponotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
make determinations often difficult. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E69EAF9E9FC75F996" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1904" box="[717,939,1575,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E69EAF9E9FC75F996" box="[717,939,1575,1598]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Camponotus xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6FBDF9E9FA46F996" authority="Dallah Torre" authorityName="Dallah Torre" box="[1178,1432,1574,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fellah">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6FBDF9E9FB22F997" box="[1178,1276,1574,1599]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">C. fellah</emphasis>
Dallah Torre
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the absence of erect setae on the ventral head surface, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFCFFF9E6F97F984FACFF9CB" box="[1200,1297,1610,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fellah">
C. 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFCFFF9E6FF6F984FACFF9CB" box="[1233,1297,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">fellah</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there are 1– 10 setae (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFCFFF9E6A27F9A0FE26F92F" author="Ionescu-Hirsch, A." box="[256,504,1646,1671]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="57 - 98" refId="ref7607" refString="Ionescu-Hirsch, A. (2009) An annotated list of Camponotus of Israel (Hymenoptera: Formicidae), with a key and descriptions of new species. Israel Journal of Entomology, 39, 57 - 98." type="journal article" year="2009">Ionescu-Hirsch, 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
